                     <title xml:lang="">trāʺ cavʻ̐ saṅʻ̨ vuñʻka vatthu</title>
                     <title xml:lang="">The sermon on the teaching of spiritual shock (saṃvega)</title>
                     
                     
                     
                     <decoNote>
                        <p>Illustrated (ornamentation): none</p>
                        <p>Illustrated (diagrams): none</p>
                        <p>Illustrated (pictures): none</p>
                     </decoNote>
                     <note>Shan text descriptor:  tra Rhyming system: samʻ kivʻ</note>
                     
                     <note>Story of a cowboy who was born from a poor family; it is the time outside the period of Buddhist teaching, but there was a Pacceka-buddha; the poor family offered alms to the Pacceka-buddha every morning; one day the cowboy found lots of gold in the field where he was feeding his cows; his family became a rich one.</note>
                     
                     <note>Subject:  sutta </note>
